	   <tr><td colspan=2>No idea of where you are, so this is what I, as a HIE mage, did....<br><br>Kel newbie area till L5 and a pet.&nbsp;&nbsp;Then down to the Butcherblocks and the creatures there...skunks, goblins, giant snakes, etc till L9.  Then I caught a ferry to Freeport and went hunting in EC for snakes, snakes and more snakes till L13.  Used a water pet of course since they are immune to poison.  I also killed some orcs when I could get a group but for some reason mages in groups aren't well loved.<br><br>At 13, off to EK.  Marvellous newbie zone, possibly the best in the game.  I bound myself beside the Gorge zone, then went hunting for snakes and spiders, anything up to light red.  If things went wrong, a quick gate to the zone, zone in, zone out, med, summon, start again.  The good part is that the Keep is quite close by for malachite and banking.  At 18ish, when I wasn't soloing crag spiders,  I hunted lions and griffawns in NK, but that is a nasty zone, so I went to LOIO at 19.  Stayed there till 26, soloing mostly.  Hard work for not a lot of returns.<br><br>After 26, I woke up to myself, caught the ferry back and went hunting in Highhold Keep.  If I couldn't get a goblin group, I soloed Osargen.  He gives xps up till 31....  At 30, down to SK and I started soloing gnolls at the spires outside Splitpaw, and avocets.  They are pretty easy once you hit 30, providing you and your pet work as a team...  <br><br>Now 38, I am still killing avocets, but I have taken side trips to Iceclad to kill snow cougars and dervishes.  Cougars are quite easy to solo at 36 or so, at least singly; dervishes are hard work.  I have managed to get the odd hill giant group in the Rathe Mountains as well.  <br><br>Once I hit 39, I am off to Velious permanently.  The Kunark mobs are way too hard by virtue of having far too many hit points.  That would not be too bad if the rewards matched up, but they don't.  Anyone that says &quot;Go to Kunark&quot;, ignore them!!<br><br>Skills?  Up to you what you want to do.  I chose alcohol tolerance.  Beware of things like jewellery, since you need to enchant bars to make decent sellable jewellery, and surprise...mages can't enchant.  Booze is mostly to be given away.  I would maybe choose tailoring or blacksmithing as a main hobby, tailoring by preference since the raw materials are easy to find.<br><br>But seriously, find your own way.  What suits me (drinking and swandiving off the Kel platforms) won't necessarily suit you.<br><br>Good luck<br>Jacynth<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
