	   <tr><td colspan=2>Focus items do not increase the lvl of the pet summoned - only increase certain stats.&nbsp;&nbsp;For instance if u summon a fire pet it will probably have more HP, Sta, or other stats.  I'm not saying those are the exact stats enhanced but u get the idea.  Also, pets do the same amount of dmg with a weapon or without unless maybe if u give em a high dmg weapon.  Meaning a 24 fire pet will hit for 22-24 max with or without summoning a spear of warding or some other weapon.  Dly is what counts - I summon daggers for my pets and they still hit for the same amount but do it a little faster.  <br><br>Also, I have been told someone in OOT sells pet spells so if ur rusty on Research try here.  Not sure where or how high the spells go to but it may help...<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
