<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100749092025583></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100749092025583><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100749092025583>RE: LVL 29 Spell</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100749092025583#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=87397><span id= >sniffynifty</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>6 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Dec 4th 1:35 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Yes, all but three level 29 mage spells can be bought at merchants: these three spells are pets that must be researched.&nbsp;&nbsp;All of the other spells can be bought, but the game makes this hard because different merchants sell different spells.<br><br>Most of your spells (Burnout II, Greater Summoning: Fire, Inferno Shield) can be purchased at most magician guilds in any city.<br><br>Two of your spells (Sword of Runes and Summon Coldstone) are only sold at special merchants, found in Ak`Anon, Erudin, and Neriak, in the spellcasters' guild.<br><br>The other three (Greater Summoning: Water, Air, and Earth) must be researched.<br><br>Hope this helps!<br><br>Rascarcapac, level 51 Elementalist, Xev Server.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
